events.1459: Bucharest chartered by Drăculeşti Vlad III, Prince of Wallachia.
events.1559: Old Court Church built by Mircea Ciobanul
events.1698: Constantin Brâncoveanu, Prince of Wallachia changed the capital from Târgoviște to Bucharest.
events.1812: City hosts signing of the Treaty of Bucharest (1812).
events.1828: City taken by Russians who handed it to the prince of Walachia in 1829.
events.1864: University of Bucharest, Bucharest National University of Arts, School of Bridges and Roads, Mines and Architecture, and National Museum of Antiquities founded.
events.1881: City becomes capital of Kingdom of Romania
events.1936: Arcul de Triumf erected on Kiseleff Road.
events.1944: Bombing of Bucharest in World War II begins.
events.1948: City becomes capital of the newly formed Romanian People's Republic.
events.1956: George Enescu Festival of music begins.
events.1994: Coat of arms of Bucharest re-adopted.
events.2007: January: Romania becomes part of the European Union.
events.2015: Colectiv nightclub fire kills at least 26 people; deadliest-ever nightclub fire in Romania and one of the deadliest incidents in the city and the country since the end of the anti-communist revolution in 1989.
